list.t:

	   The Expiry Time is displayed as a compact numeric-only representation of ISO 8601. All punctuation is removed. This form is slightly different than the recommendation in  but is common for DNS protocols. It is defined in Section 3.2 of  as YYYYMMDDHHmmSS in UTC. This form will always be exactly 14 digits since no component is optional.


      YYYY is the year;

      MM is the month number (01-12);

      DD is the day of the month (01-31);

      HH is the hour, in 24 hour notation (00-23);

      mm is the minute (00-59); and

      SS is the second (00-60) where 60 is only possible as a leap second.

